AFM Uluslararasi Film Produksiyon
Ticaret & Sanayi AS (AFMAS) , a Turkish cinema operator, rose in Istanbul
after owner Esas Holding AS completed the sale of a 40 percent
stake in the unit for $39.9 million, or $7.47 a share.  AFM Film gained 2.3 percent to 13.65 liras at the close.
Esas completed the second phase of the stake sale in AFM Film to
Mars Sinema & Sportif Tesisler Isletmeciligi AS, raising Marsâ€™s
ownership to 89 percent, AFM said in a statement to the  Istanbul
Stock Exchange  after the market closed yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
